Building and Installing The Clans
===============================================================================


QUICK START
===============================================================================

  make -j8
  make install

  Optional: install devkit tools for content creation:

    make install-devkit

  Note: On BSD systems (FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD, etc.), substitute 'gmake'
  for 'make' in all commands below.

  By default, installation goes to /opt/clans/.  To install to a different
  directory (e.g., for a Synchronet BBS):

    make install INSTALLDIR=/sbbs/xtrn/clans


PREREQUISITES
===============================================================================

  Required:
    - C17 compiler (GCC or Clang)
    - GNU make
    - POSIX-compatible system (FreeBSD, Linux, macOS, Windows with MinGW)

  The OpenDoors library is included in this distribution and statically
  linked into the binaries, so no separate installation or configuration
  is required.

  Optional (for devkit):
    - Unix shell environment (for integration tests)


BUILDING
===============================================================================

  Build the game only:

    make -j8

  Build the devkit tools only:

    make -j8 devkit

  Build both game and devkit:

    make -j8 all

  Debug build (with symbols and compiler warnings):

    make -j8 DEBUG=1

  Windows (native build):
    Open src/clans.sln in Visual Studio and build.

  Windows (cross-compilation from Linux/FreeBSD, from src/ directory):

    make -j8 CC=x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc         # Win64
    make -j8 CC=i686-w64-mingw32-gcc           # Win32

  Test the build:

    make test


INSTALLING
===============================================================================

  Install the game to a staging directory (for packaging):

    make install DESTDIR=/tmp/staging PREFIX=/opt

  This installs to:  /tmp/staging/opt/clans/

  Install directly to system (requires privilege):

    make install PREFIX=/opt

  This installs to:  /opt/clans/


DEVKIT INSTALLATION
===============================================================================

  The devkit (quest compiler tools) is optional.  Install it separately:

    make install-devkit DESTDIR=/tmp/staging PREFIX=/opt

  Installs to:  /tmp/staging/opt/clans/


UNINSTALLING
===============================================================================

  Remove the game:

    make uninstall PREFIX=/opt

  Remove the devkit:

    make uninstall-devkit PREFIX=/opt


INSTALL OPTIONS
===============================================================================

  INSTALLDIR      Installation directory (default: /opt/clans/)
                  Simplest option for end users:

                    make install INSTALLDIR=/usr/local/clans/

  PREFIX          Parent directory (default: /opt)
                  Game installs to: $(PREFIX)/clans/

  DESTDIR         Staging root for packagers (default: empty)
                  Used with PREFIX: $(DESTDIR)$(PREFIX)/clans/

  Example (packager build):

    make install DESTDIR=/tmp/buildroot PREFIX=/usr/games
    # Installs to: /tmp/buildroot/usr/games/clans/


DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
===============================================================================

  The installation creates clans/ containing:

    Game binaries and wrappers:
      clans, reset, config, pcedit (wrapper scripts/executables)
      clans.<os>.<machine>.<flavour>, reset.<os>.<machine>.<flavour>, etc.
      install (wrapper script/executable)

    Game data:
      clans.pak (compiled game data)
      outbound/ (game data directory)

    Game documentation and configuration:
      clans.txt, player.txt, whatsnew.txt, questgen.txt, prompt.md
      quests.ini, quests.hlp, clans.ini, route.smp, worldndx.smp
      clanad.ans, lockout.txt, news.txt, runclans.bat

  With devkit, additional tools and files are installed:

    Devkit tool wrappers and binaries:
      chew, langcomp, mcomp, mitems, mspells, mclass, makenpc
      ecomp, makepak, qtest (wrapper scripts/executables)
      chew.<os>.<machine>.<flavour>, langcomp.<os>.<machine>.<flavour>, etc.

    Devkit documentation and example files:
      clandev.txt, utf8.txt, qtest-scripting.txt, example.ini
      pak.lst, genall.mak, genall.bat
      event1.evt, event2.evt, event3.evt, event4.evt, event5.evt


PLATFORM NOTES
===============================================================================

  POSIX systems (Linux, FreeBSD, macOS, OpenBSD, NetBSD, etc.):
    Standard POSIX build.  GCC or Clang both work.
    On BSD systems, use 'gmake' instead of 'make' in all commands.

  Windows:
    Native build: Open src/clans.sln in Visual Studio.
    Cross-compile from Linux/FreeBSD: Use MinGW64 with make.
    Installation uses make (not supported natively on Windows).


TROUBLESHOOTING
===============================================================================

  Build fails with "make: not found":
    Install GNU make (FreeBSD: pkg install gmake, Linux: apt install make)

  Build fails with compiler error about stdint.h:
    Ensure C17 or later compiler (gcc -std=c17, clang -std=c17)

  Install fails with permission denied:
    Use DESTDIR for staging: make install DESTDIR=/tmp/staging

  For detailed build information, consult docs/notes.txt
